The paper deals with the problem of visualizing large-scale and high-dimensional data, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of probabilistic models and optimization techniques, which are common in sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the construction of a K-nearest neighbor graph, which is a common technique in sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
